column9: description_of_origin
A http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/vbo#origindescription
Brazilian dairy breed created by crossing Gir and Holstein (3/8 Gir, 5/8 Holstein)
Hardy beef breed from Russia and Kazakhstan.
Local Romanian milk breed, the result of crossbreeding between Braunvieh and local Mocanita and Grey cattle.
Indigenous Iranian breed raised for meat, milk, and fiber (mohair).
Israeli sheep breed that is a product of crossbreeding Awassi and East Friesian; dual purpose milk and meat breed with white wool
One of the main sheep breeds in Egypt, well-adapted to the desert environment.
Hardy French breed characterized by brownish-black wool, prolificacy, and good milk production.
Czech breed originated from a native breed improved by crossing with German Brown bucks.
Australian meat sheep breed derived from selective breeding of White Dorper, Van Rooy, Poll Dorset, and Texel.
French sheep breed originating from the southern part of the Massif Central. Known for its hardiness and adaptibility to harsh conditions.
Dairy breed combining an extensive infusion of Scandinavian Red genetics with other Australian Red breeds such as Ayrshire, Dairy or Milking Shorthorn, Illawarra, or Red and White Holstein.
Holstein x Sahiwal crossbred
Dairy breed that originated in the North Sea coast regions of northern Germany and the Netherlands.
Japanese dual-purpose breed; excellent layers of light brown eggs
Extremely rare, dual-purpose breed that originated in South Korea.
Ancient Italian dual-purpose crested chicken breed; has two recognized colors, black and white.
Chinese indigenous breed from Qingyuan County, Guangdong Province.
Dual-purpose, medium-sized goat breed from India.
Ethiopian goat breed related to Western Highland and Keffa.
Indigenous goat breed from Iran that produces high-quality cashmere.
Dual-purpose (milk and meat) breed indigenous to India.
May belong to ether of two closely related and interconnected breeds: Norsk Kalkblodstraver (Norwegian Coldblood Trotter) or Svensk Kallblodstravare (Swedish Coldblood Trotter)
Chinese indigenous breed known for high prolificacy, superior meat quality, and adaptation to harsh environments.
Native Indian breed with good wool and milk production.
Medium-sized, light brown sheep breed native to India; body is covered with very short hair which is not shorn; skin highly prized for leather.
Largest and heaviest sheep breed in India; well-adapted to heat and humidity.
Breed resulting from successive crosses between 1/2 Romanov and 1/2 Berrichon du Cher animals (formerly INRA 401).
Composite Indian breed with 50-75% Bos taurus ancestry (Holstein-Friesian, Brown Swiss, Jersey) and 25-50% Bos indicus (Hariana)

Heat tolerant, hardy breed used for milk, meat and draft; usually red or gray in color with horns, loose skin, large ears, and a hump above their shoulders. NOTE: "Zebu" can also be used as a general term for breeds such as Brahman, Gir, Guzera, and Nelore.
Iranian dual-purpose native breed, resilient to harsh environments.
Chinese breed comprised of 25% Chinese Huai and 75% Large White
Fast-growing meat and wool breed developed in India by crossing Nali, Merino and Corriedale with inheritance of 37.5% Nali and 62.5% exotic inheritance.
